H0.text: To ‘Defenestrate’ is to throw something or someone out of what. A door

H1.text: To ‘Defenestrate’ is to throw something or someone out of what. A balcony

H2.text: To ‘Defenestrate’ is to throw something or someone out of what. A roof

H3.text: To ‘Defenestrate’ is to throw something or someone out of what. A window

A4.text: Defenestration (from Neo-Latin de fenestrā) is the act of throwing someone or something out of a window.

A5.text: The word itself is derived from Neo-Latin defenestratio; with dē meaning 'out' + fenestra meaning 'window' + -atio as a suffix indicating an action or process.
